rsIpsecSaMonModule.name: rsIpsecSaMonModule
rsIpsecSaMonModule.contactinfo: Ella Yu WatchGuard Technologies, Inc. 1841 Zanker Road San Jose, CA 95112 USA 408-519-4888 ella.yu@watchguard.com
rsIpsecSaMonModule.description: The MIB module describes generic IPSec objects defined in IETF working draft 'draft-ieft-ipsec-monitor-mib-01' and RapidStream's extension.

IpsecSaCreatorIdent.name: IpsecSaCreatorIdent
IpsecSaCreatorIdent.description: A value indicating how an SA was created.

IpsecIpv6Address.name: IpsecIpv6Address
IpsecIpv6Address.description: This data type is used to model IPv6 address prefixes. This is a binary string of 16 octets in network byte-order.

rsIpsecSaMonitorMIB.name: rsIpsecSaMonitorMIB
rsIpsecSaMonitorMIB.description: This is the base object identifier for all IPSec branches.

rsSaTables.name: rsSaTables
rsSaTables.description: This is the base object identifier for all SA tables.

rsSaStatistics.name: rsSaStatistics
rsSaStatistics.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which are global counters for IPSec security associations.

rsSaErrors.name: rsSaErrors
rsSaErrors.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which are global error counters for IPSec security associations.

rsSaTraps.name: rsSaTraps
rsSaTraps.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which are traps for IPSec security associations.

rsSaTrapObjects.name: rsSaTrapObjects
rsSaTrapObjects.description: This is the base object identifier for objects which are used as part of traps.

rsSaTrapControl.name: rsSaTrapControl
rsSaTrapControl.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which are trap controls for IPSec security associations.

rsSaGroups.name: rsSaGroups
rsSaGroups.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which describe the groups in this MIB.

rsSaConformance.name: rsSaConformance
rsSaConformance.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which describe the conformance for this MIB.

rsIpsecSaEspInTable.name: rsIpsecSaEspInTable
rsIpsecSaEspInTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing information on IPSec inbound ESP SAs. There should be one row for every inbound ESP security association that exists in the entity. The maximum number of rows is implementation dependent.

rsIpsecSaEspInEntry.name: rsIpsecSaEspInEntry
rsIpsecSaEspInEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the information on a particular IPSec inbound ESP SA. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

rsIpsecSaEspInAddress.name: rsIpsecSaEspInAddress
rsIpsecSaEspInAddress.description: The destination address of the SA. For implementations that do not support IPv6, this address should appear as one of the IPv4-mapped IPv6 addresses as defined in Section 2.5.4 of [IPV6AA]. Specifically, the prefix '0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:FFFF:' is used for IPv4 only nodes, while the prefix '0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:' is used for bi-lingual nodes.

rsIpsecSaEspInSpi.name: rsIpsecSaEspInSpi
rsIpsecSaEspInSpi.description: The security parameters index of the SA.

rsIpsecSaEspInDestId.name: rsIpsecSaEspInDestId
rsIpsecSaEspInDestId.description: The destination identifier of the SA, or 0 if unknown or if the SA uses transport mode encapsulation. This value is taken directly from the optional ID payloads that are exchanged during SA creation negotiation.

rsIpsecSaEspInDestIdType.name: rsIpsecSaEspInDestIdType
rsIpsecSaEspInDestIdType.description: The type of identifier presented by 'rsIpsecSaEspInDestId', or 0 if unknown or if the SA uses transport mode encapsulation.

rsIpsecSaEspInSourceId.name: rsIpsecSaEspInSourceId
rsIpsecSaEspInSourceId.description: The source identifier of the SA, or 0 if unknown or if the SA uses transport mode encapsulation. This value is taken directly from the optional ID payloads that are exchange during SA creation negotiation.

rsIpsecSaEspInSourceIdType.name: rsIpsecSaEspInSourceIdType
rsIpsecSaEspInSourceIdType.description: The type of identifier presented by 'rsIpsecSaEspInSourceId', or 0 if unknown or if the SA uses transport mode encapsulation.

rsIpsecSaEspInProtocol.name: rsIpsecSaEspInProtocol
rsIpsecSaEspInProtocol.description: The transport-layer protocol number that this SA carries, or 0 if it carries any protocol.

rsIpsecSaEspInDestPort.name: rsIpsecSaEspInDestPort
rsIpsecSaEspInDestPort.description: The destination port number of the protocol that this SA carries, or 0 if it carries any port number.

rsIpsecSaEspInSourcePort.name: rsIpsecSaEspInSourcePort
rsIpsecSaEspInSourcePort.description: The source port number of the protocol that this SA carries, or 0 if it carries any port number.

rsIpsecSaEspInCreator.name: rsIpsecSaEspInCreator
rsIpsecSaEspInCreator.description: The creator of this SA. This MIB makes no assumptions about how the SAs are created. They may be created statically, or by a key exchange protocol such as IKE, or by some other method.

rsIpsecSaEspInEncapsulation.name: rsIpsecSaEspInEncapsulation
rsIpsecSaEspInEncapsulation.description: The type of encapsulation used by this SA.

rsIpsecSaEspInEncAlg.name: rsIpsecSaEspInEncAlg
rsIpsecSaEspInEncAlg.description: A unique value representing the encryption algorithm applied to traffic or 0 if there is no encryption used.

rsIpsecSaEspInEncKeyLength.name: rsIpsecSaEspInEncKeyLength
rsIpsecSaEspInEncKeyLength.description: The length of the encryption key in bits used for the algorithm specified in the 'rsIpsecSaEspInEncAlg' object, or 0 if the key length is implicit in the specified algorithm or there is no encryption specified.

rsIpsecSaEspInAuthAlg.name: rsIpsecSaEspInAuthAlg
rsIpsecSaEspInAuthAlg.description: A unique value representing the hash algorithm applied to traffic or 0 if there is no authentication used.

rsIpsecSaEspInLimitSeconds.name: rsIpsecSaEspInLimitSeconds
rsIpsecSaEspInLimitSeconds.description: The maximum lifetime in seconds of the SA, or 0 if there is no time constraint on its expiration. The display value is limited to 4294967295 seconds (more than 136 years); values greater than that value will be truncated.

rsIpsecSaEspInLimitKbytes.name: rsIpsecSaEspInLimitKbytes
rsIpsecSaEspInLimitKbytes.description: The maximum traffic in kilobytes that the SA is allowed to support, or 0 if there is no traffic constraint on its expiration. The display value is limited to 4294967295 kilobytes; values greater than that value will be truncated.

rsIpsecSaEspInAccSeconds.name: rsIpsecSaEspInAccSeconds
rsIpsecSaEspInAccSeconds.description: The number of seconds accumulated against the SA's expiration by time. This is also the number of seconds that the SA has existed.

rsIpsecSaEspInAccKbytes.name: rsIpsecSaEspInAccKbytes
rsIpsecSaEspInAccKbytes.description: The amount of traffic accumulated that counts against the SA's expiration by traffic limitation, measured in Kbytes. This value may be 0 if the SA does not expire based on traffic.

rsIpsecSaEspInUserOctets.name: rsIpsecSaEspInUserOctets
rsIpsecSaEspInUserOctets.description: The amount of user level traffic measured in bytes handled by the SA. This is not necessarily the same as the amount of traffic applied against the traffic expiration limit.

rsIpsecSaEspInPackets.name: rsIpsecSaEspInPackets
rsIpsecSaEspInPackets.description: The number of packets handled by the SA.

rsIpsecSaEspInDecryptErrors.name: rsIpsecSaEspInDecryptErrors
rsIpsecSaEspInDecryptErrors.description: The number of packets discarded by the SA due to decryption errors.

rsIpsecSaEspInAuthErrors.name: rsIpsecSaEspInAuthErrors
rsIpsecSaEspInAuthErrors.description: The number of packets discarded by the SA due to authentication errors.

rsIpsecSaEspInReplayErrors.name: rsIpsecSaEspInReplayErrors
rsIpsecSaEspInReplayErrors.description: The number of packets discarded by the SA due to replay errors.

rsIpsecSaEspInPolicyErrors.name: rsIpsecSaEspInPolicyErrors
rsIpsecSaEspInPolicyErrors.description: The number of packets discarded by the SA due to policy errors. This includes packets where the next protocol is invalid.

rsIpsecSaEspInPadErrors.name: rsIpsecSaEspInPadErrors
rsIpsecSaEspInPadErrors.description: The number of packets discarded by the SA due to pad value errors. Implementations that do not check this must not support this object.

rsIpsecSaEspInOtherReceiveErrors.name: rsIpsecSaEspInOtherReceiveErrors
rsIpsecSaEspInOtherReceiveErrors.description: The number of packets discarded by the SA due to errors other than decryption, authentication or replay errors. This may include packets dropped due to a lack of receive buffers, and may include packets dropped due to congestion at the decryption element.

rsIpsecSaIpcompInCpi.name: rsIpsecSaIpcompInCpi
rsIpsecSaIpcompInCpi.description: The CPI of the SA. Since the lower values of CPIs are reserved to be the same as the algorithm, the syntax for this object is the same as the transform.

rsIpsecSaIpcompInDestId.name: rsIpsecSaIpcompInDestId

This value, if non-zero, is taken directly from the optional ID payloads that are exchange during SA creation negotiation.

rsIpsecSaAhOutLimitKbytes.description: The maximum traffic in Kbytes that the SA is allowed to support, or 0 if there is no traffic constraint on its expiration. The display value is limited to 4294967295 kilobytes; values greater than that value will be truncated.

rsIpsecSaAhOutAccSeconds.name: rsIpsecSaAhOutAccSeconds
rsIpsecSaAhOutAccSeconds.description: The number of seconds accumulated against the SA's expiration by time. This is also the number of seconds that the SA has existed.

rsIpsecSaAhOutAccKbytes.name: rsIpsecSaAhOutAccKbytes
rsIpsecSaAhOutAccKbytes.description: The amount of traffic accumulated that counts against the SA's expiration by traffic limitation, measured in Kbytes. This value may be 0 if the SA does not expire based on traffic.

rsIpsecSaAhOutUserOctets.name: rsIpsecSaAhOutUserOctets
rsIpsecSaAhOutUserOctets.description: The amount of user level traffic measured in bytes handled by the SA. This is not necessarily the same as the amount of traffic applied against the traffic expiration limit.

rsIpsecSaAhOutPackets.name: rsIpsecSaAhOutPackets
rsIpsecSaAhOutPackets.description: The number of packets handled by the SA.

rsIpsecSaAhOutSendErrors.name: rsIpsecSaAhOutSendErrors
rsIpsecSaAhOutSendErrors.description: The number of packets discarded by the SA due to any error. This may include errors due to a lack of transmit buffers.

rsIpsecSaIpcompOutTable.name: rsIpsecSaIpcompOutTable
rsIpsecSaIpcompOutTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing information on IPSec Outbound IPCOMP SAs. There should be one row for every outbound IPCOMP (security) association that exists in the entity. The maximum number of rows is implementation dependent.

rsIpsecSaIpcompOutEntry.name: rsIpsecSaIpcompOutEntry
rsIpsecSaIpcompOutEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the information on a particular IPSec Outbound IPCOMP SA. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

rsIpsecSaIpcompOutAddress.name: rsIpsecSaIpcompOutAddress
rsIpsecSaIpcompOutAddress.description: The destination address of the SA. If the IPCOMP SA is shared across multiple SAs in protection suites, this value may be 0. For implementations that do not support IPv6, this address should appear as one of the IPv4-mapped IPv6 addresses as defined in Section 2.5.4 of [IPV6AA]. Specifically, the prefix '0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:FFFF:' is used for IPv4 only nodes, while the prefix '0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:' is used for bi-lingual nodes.

rsIpsecSaIpcompOutCpi.name: rsIpsecSaIpcompOutCpi
rsIpsecSaIpcompOutCpi.description: The CPI of the SA. Since the lower values of CPIs are reserved to be the same as the algorithm, the syntax for this object is the same as the transform.

rsIpsecSaIpcompOutSourceId.name: rsIpsecSaIpcompOutSourceId
rsIpsecSaIpcompOutSourceId.description: The source identifier of the SA, or 0 if unknown or if the SA uses transport mode encapsulation, or 0 if this SA is used with multiple SAs in protection suites. This value, if non-zero, is taken directly from the optional ID payloads that are exchange during phase 2 negotiations.

rsIpsecSaIpcompOutSourceIdType.name: rsIpsecSaIpcompOutSourceIdType
rsIpsecSaIpcompOutSourceIdType.description: The type of identifier presented by 'rsIpsecSaIpcompOutSourceId', or 0 if unknown or if the SA uses transport mode encapsulation, or 0 if this SA is used with multiple SAs in protection suites.

rsIpsecSaIpcompOutDestId.name: rsIpsecSaIpcompOutDestId
rsIpsecSaIpcompOutDestId.description: The destination identifier of the SA, or 0 if unknown or if the SA uses transport mode encapsulation, or 0 if this SA is used with multiple SAs in protection suites. This value, if non-zero, is taken directly from the optional ID payloads that are exchange during phase 2 negotiations.

rsIpsecSaIpcompOutDestIdType.name: rsIpsecSaIpcompOutDestIdType
rsIpsecSaIpcompOutDestIdType.description: The type of identifier presented by 'rsIpsecSaIpcompOutDestId', or 0 if unknown or if the SA uses transport mode encapsulation, or 0 if this SA is used with multiple SAs in protection suites.

rsIpsecSaIpcompOutProtocol.name: rsIpsecSaIpcompOutProtocol
rsIpsecSaIpcompOutProtocol.description: The transport-layer protocol number that this SA carries, or 0 if it carries any protocol.

rsIpsecSaIpcompOutSourcePort.name: rsIpsecSaIpcompOutSourcePort
rsIpsecSaIpcompOutSourcePort.description: The source port number of the protocol that this SA carries, or 0 if it carries any port number.

rsIpsecSaIpcompOutDestPort.name: rsIpsecSaIpcompOutDestPort
rsIpsecSaIpcompOutDestPort.description: The destination port number of the protocol that this SA carries, or 0 if it carries any port number.

rsIpsecSaIpcompOutCreator.name: rsIpsecSaIpcompOutCreator
rsIpsecSaIpcompOutCreator.description: The creator of this SA. This MIB makes no assumptions about how the SAs are created. They may be created statically, or by a key exchange protocol such as IKE, or by some other method.

rsIpsecSaIpcompOutEncapsulation.name: rsIpsecSaIpcompOutEncapsulation
rsIpsecSaIpcompOutEncapsulation.description: The type of encapsulation used by this SA.

rsIpsecSaIpcompOutCompAlg.name: rsIpsecSaIpcompOutCompAlg
rsIpsecSaIpcompOutCompAlg.description: A unique value representing the compression algorithm applied to traffic.

rsIpsecSaIpcompOutSeconds.name: rsIpsecSaIpcompOutSeconds
rsIpsecSaIpcompOutSeconds.description: The number of seconds that the SA has existed.

rsIpsecSaIpcompOutUserOctets.name: rsIpsecSaIpcompOutUserOctets
rsIpsecSaIpcompOutUserOctets.description: The amount of user level traffic measured in bytes handled by the SA. This is not necessarily the same as the amount of traffic applied against the traffic expiration limit.

rsIpsecSaIpcompOutPackets.name: rsIpsecSaIpcompOutPackets
rsIpsecSaIpcompOutPackets.description: The number of packets handled by the SA.

rsIpsecEspCurrentInboundSAs.name: rsIpsecEspCurrentInboundSAs
rsIpsecEspCurrentInboundSAs.description: The current number of inbound ESP SAs in the entity.

rsIpsecEspTotalInboundSAs.name: rsIpsecEspTotalInboundSAs
rsIpsecEspTotalInboundSAs.description: The total number of inbound ESP SAs created in the entity since boot time.

rsIpsecEspCurrentOutboundSAs.name: rsIpsecEspCurrentOutboundSAs
rsIpsecEspCurrentOutboundSAs.description: The current number of outbound ESP SAs in the entity.

rsIpsecEspTotalOutboundSAs.name: rsIpsecEspTotalOutboundSAs
rsIpsecEspTotalOutboundSAs.description: The total number of outbound ESP SAs created in the entity since boot time.

rsIpsecAhCurrentInboundSAs.name: rsIpsecAhCurrentInboundSAs
rsIpsecAhCurrentInboundSAs.description: The current number of inbound AH SAs in the entity.

rsIpsecAhTotalInboundSAs.name: rsIpsecAhTotalInboundSAs
rsIpsecAhTotalInboundSAs.description: The total number of inbound AH SAs created in the entity since boot time.

rsIpsecAhCurrentOutboundSAs.name: rsIpsecAhCurrentOutboundSAs
rsIpsecAhCurrentOutboundSAs.description: The current number of outbound AH SAs in the entity.

rsIpsecAhTotalOutboundSAs.name: rsIpsecAhTotalOutboundSAs
rsIpsecAhTotalOutboundSAs.description: The total number of outbound AH SAs created in the entity since boot time.

rsIpsecIpcompCurrentInboundSAs.name: rsIpsecIpcompCurrentInboundSAs
rsIpsecIpcompCurrentInboundSAs.description: The current number of inbound IPCOMP SAs in the entity.

rsIpsecIpcompTotalInboundSAs.name: rsIpsecIpcompTotalInboundSAs
rsIpsecIpcompTotalInboundSAs.description: The total number of inbound IPCOMP SAs created in the entity since boot time.

rsIpsecIpcompCurrentOutboundSAs.name: rsIpsecIpcompCurrentOutboundSAs
rsIpsecIpcompCurrentOutboundSAs.description: The current number of outbound IPCOMP SAs in the entity.

rsIpsecIpcompTotalOutboundSAs.name: rsIpsecIpcompTotalOutboundSAs
rsIpsecIpcompTotalOutboundSAs.description: The total number of outbound IPCOMP SAs created in the entity since boot time.

rsIpsecDecryptionErrors.name: rsIpsecDecryptionErrors
rsIpsecDecryptionErrors.description: The total number of packets received by the entity in SAs since boot time with decryption errors.

rsIpsecAuthenticationErrors.name: rsIpsecAuthenticationErrors
rsIpsecAuthenticationErrors.description: The total number of packets received by the entity in SAs since boot time with authentication errors. This includes all packets in which the hash value is determined to be invalid, for both ESP and AH SAs.

rsIpsecReplayErrors.name: rsIpsecReplayErrors
rsIpsecReplayErrors.description: The total number of packets received by the entity in SAs since boot time with replay errors.

rsIpsecPolicyErrors.name: rsIpsecPolicyErrors
rsIpsecPolicyErrors.description: The total number of packets received by the entity in SAs since boot time and discarded due to policy errors. This includes packets that had selectors that were invalid for the SA that carried them.

rsIpsecOtherReceiveErrors.name: rsIpsecOtherReceiveErrors
rsIpsecOtherReceiveErrors.description: The total number of packets received by the entity in SAs since boot time and discarded due to errors not due to decryption, authentication, replay or policy.

rsIpsecSendErrors.name: rsIpsecSendErrors
rsIpsecSendErrors.description: The total number of packets to be sent by the entity in SAs since boot time and discarded due to errors.

rsIpsecUnknownSpiErrors.name: rsIpsecUnknownSpiErrors
rsIpsecUnknownSpiErrors.description: The total number of packets received by the entity since boot time with SPIs or CPIs that were not valid.

rsIpsecSecurityProtocol.name: rsIpsecSecurityProtocol
rsIpsecSecurityProtocol.description: A security protocol associated with the trap.

rsIpsecSPI.name: rsIpsecSPI
rsIpsecSPI.description: An SPI associated with a trap. Where the security protocol associated with the trap is IPCOMP, this value has a maximum of 65535.

rsIpsecLocalAddress.name: rsIpsecLocalAddress
rsIpsecLocalAddress.description: A local IP address associated with the trap.

rsIpsecPeerAddress.name: rsIpsecPeerAddress
rsIpsecPeerAddress.description: A peer IP address associated with the trap.

rsEspAuthFailureTrapEnable.name: rsEspAuthFailureTrapEnable
rsEspAuthFailureTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether espAuthFailureTrap traps should be generated.

rsAhAuthFailureTrapEnable.name: rsAhAuthFailureTrapEnable
rsAhAuthFailureTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether ahAuthFailureTrap traps should be generated.

rsEspReplayFailureTrapEnable.name: rsEspReplayFailureTrapEnable
rsEspReplayFailureTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether espReplayFailureTrap traps should be generated.

rsAhReplayFailureTrapEnable.name: rsAhReplayFailureTrapEnable
rsAhReplayFailureTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether ahReplayFailureTrap traps should be generated.

rsEspPolicyFailureTrapEnable.name: rsEspPolicyFailureTrapEnable
rsEspPolicyFailureTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether espPolicyFailureTrap traps should be generated.

rsAhPolicyFailureTrapEnable.name: rsAhPolicyFailureTrapEnable
rsAhPolicyFailureTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether ahPolicyFailureTrap traps should be generated.

rsInvalidSpiTrapEnable.name: rsInvalidSpiTrapEnable
rsInvalidSpiTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether invalidSpiTrap traps should be generated.

rsEspAuthFailureTrap.name: rsEspAuthFailureTrap
rsEspAuthFailureTrap.description: IPSec packets with invalid hashes were found in an inbound ESP SA. The total number of authentication errors accumulated is sent for the specific row of the 'rsIpsecSaEspInTable' table for the SA; this provides the identity of the SA in which the error occurred. Implementations SHOULD send one trap per SA (within a reasonable time period), rather than sending one trap per packet.

rsAhAuthFailureTrap.name: rsAhAuthFailureTrap
rsAhAuthFailureTrap.description: IPSec packets with invalid hashes were found in an inbound AH SA. The total number of authentication errors accumulated is sent for the specific row of the 'rsIpsecSaAhInTable' table for the SA; this provides the identity of the SA in which the error occurred. Implementations SHOULD send one trap per SA (within a reasonable time period), rather than sending one trap per packet.

rsEspReplayFailureTrap.name: rsEspReplayFailureTrap
rsEspReplayFailureTrap.description: IPSec packets with invalid sequence numbers were found in an inbound ESP SA. The total number of replay errors accumulated is sent for the specific row of the 'rsIpsecSaEspInTable' table for the SA; this provides the identity of the SA in which the error occurred. Implementations SHOULD send one trap per SA (within a reasonable time period), rather than sending one trap per packet.

rsAhReplayFailureTrap.name: rsAhReplayFailureTrap
rsAhReplayFailureTrap.description: IPSec packets with invalid sequence numbers were found in the specified AH SA. The total number of replay errors accumulated is sent for the specific row of the 'rsIpsecSaAhInTable' table for the SA; this provides the identity of the SA in which the error occurred. Implementations SHOULD send one trap per SA (within a reasonable time period), rather than sending one trap per packet.

rsEspPolicyFailureTrap.name: rsEspPolicyFailureTrap
rsEspPolicyFailureTrap.description: IPSec packets carrying packets with invalid selectors for the specified ESP SA were found. The total number of policy errors accumulated is sent for the specific row of the 'rsIpsecSaEspInTable' table for the SA; this provides the identity of the SA in which the error occurred. Implementations SHOULD send one trap per SA (within a reasonable time period), rather than sending one trap per packet.

rsAhPolicyFailureTrap.name: rsAhPolicyFailureTrap
rsAhPolicyFailureTrap.description: IPSec packets carrying packets with invalid selectors for the specified AH SA were found. The total number of policy errors accumulated is sent for the specific row of the 'rsIpsecSaAhInTable' table for the SA; this provides the identity of the SA in which the error occurred. Implementations SHOULD send one trap per SA (within a reasonable time period), rather than sending one trap per packet.

rsInvalidSpiTrap.name: rsInvalidSpiTrap
rsInvalidSpiTrap.description: A packet with an unknown SPI was detected from the specified peer with the specified SPI using the specified protocol. The destination address of the received packet is specified by 'ipsecLocalAddress'. The value 'ifIndex' may be 0 if this optional linkage is unsupported. If the object 'ipsecSecurityProtocol' has the value for IPCOMP, then the 'ipsecSPI' object is the CPI of the packet. Implementations SHOULD send one trap per peer (within a reasonable time period), rather than sending one trap per packet.
